<p class="title">Chapter 8: Maid's Diary: Fateful Parting (No.08)</p>
<p class="para">XX/XX<br>Rain<br><br>The princess was suddenly married off to a king of a faraway<br>land. Forward of me though it was, I pleaded with the queen<br>to remain in the princess's service, but she disapproved. <br><br>But why? I have been the closest to the princess thus far<br>and have cared for her like no other.<br><br>Today, the queen ordered me to clean up the princess's room.<br>Indeed, she may come home one day. It must be spotless for<br>her return.<br><br>Her bed looks so inviting. I don't suppose she would mind<br>if I lay on it just a little, would she?</p>
